title: Grateful Dead Live at Bayfront Center Arena on 1988-10-15
description:
Set 1

The Music Never Stopped
Sugaree
Blow Away
Walkin' Blues
When Push Comes To Shove
Queen Jane Approximately
Tennessee Jed
Let it Grow

Set 2

One More Saturday Night
Crazy Fingers
Playing In The Band
Uncle John's Band
Drums
Space
Truckin'
Smokestack Lightning
Stella Blue
Turn On Your Lovelight

Encore:
U.S. Blues

Jerry Garcia - Guitar
Bob Weir - Guitar
Brent Mydland - Keyboards
Phil Lesh - Bass
Bill Kreutzmann - Drums
Mickey Hart - Drums

reviews.review_text:
First known audio documentation of Bobby having that ponytail Listen to the pre-song crowd audio at the start of set one. 

You'll hear somebody noting the ponytail. 

Otherwise, it's hard to get close to this show because there's no (available [yet?]) ultramatrix. The show itself sounds like your typical 1988 party, solid enough, not necessarily that significant as a recording 30 years later. Completists, sure. Ppl who were in attendance, sure. The rest of us? Nobody needs to make hearing this show a priority, IMO
